<section class="detail" id="fetch/2">


  <div class="detail-header">
    <a href="#fetch/2" class="detail-link" data-no-tooltip="" aria-label="Link to this function">
      <i class="ri-link-m" aria-hidden="true"></i>
    </a>
    <div class="heading-with-actions">

      <div class="signature-row">


            <h1 class="signature" translate="no">fetch(Orddict :: <a href="#t:orddict/2">orddict</a>(Key, Value))<span class="signature-arrow">&nbsp;-&gt;&nbsp;</span><span class="signature-result">Value</span></h1>




          <a href="https://github.com/erlang/otp/blob/master/lib/stdlib/src/orddict.erl#L189" class="icon-action" rel="help nofollow" aria-label="View Source">
            <i class="ri-code-s-slash-line" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="docstring">



<p>Returns the value associated with <code class="inline">Key</code> in dictionary <code class="inline">Orddict</code>.</p><p>This function assumes that the <code class="inline">Key</code> is present in the dictionary. An
exception is generated if <code class="inline">Key</code> is not in the dictionary.</p><h2 id="fetch/2-examples" class="section-heading"><a href="#fetch/2-examples" class="hover-link"><i class="ri-link-m" aria-hidden="true"></i></a><span class="text">Examples</span></h2><pre><code class="makeup erlang" translate="no"><span class="gp unselectable">1&gt; </span><span class="n">OrdDict1</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">=</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nc">orddict</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nf">from_list</span><span class="p" data-group-id="3492762560-1">(</span><span class="p" data-group-id="3492762560-2">[</span><span class="p" data-group-id="3492762560-3">{</span><span class="ss">a</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p" data-group-id="3492762560-3">}</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="p" data-group-id="3492762560-4">{</span><span class="ss">b</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p" data-group-id="3492762560-4">}</span><span class="p" data-group-id="3492762560-2">]</span><span class="p" data-group-id="3492762560-1">)</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="p" data-group-id="3492762560-5">[</span><span class="p" data-group-id="3492762560-6">{</span><span class="ss">a</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p" data-group-id="3492762560-6">}</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="p" data-group-id="3492762560-7">{</span><span class="ss">b</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p" data-group-id="3492762560-7">}</span><span class="p" data-group-id="3492762560-5">]</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="gp unselectable">2&gt; </span><span class="nc">orddict</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nf">fetch</span><span class="p" data-group-id="3492762560-8">(</span><span class="ss">a</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n">OrdDict1</span><span class="p" data-group-id="3492762560-8">)</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="gp unselectable">3&gt; </span><span class="nc">orddict</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nf">fetch</span><span class="p" data-group-id="3492762560-9">(</span><span class="ss">missing</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n">OrdDict1</span><span class="p" data-group-id="3492762560-9">)</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="gt">** exception error: no function clause matching orddict:fetch(missing,[])</span></code></pre>
  </section>
</section>
